  "prompt": "How do I get over my nervousness?",
  "response": "Here are some effective strategies to help manage nervousness:\n\n1. Practice deep breathing techniques\n- Slow, deep breaths can calm your nervous system\n- Try 4-7-8 breathing method\n\n2. Prepare thoroughly\n- Being well-prepared increases confidence\n- Practice or rehearse beforehand\n\n3. Use positive self-talk\n- Replace negative thoughts with encouraging statements\n- Remind yourself of past successes\n\n4. Exercise regularly\n- Physical activity reduces stress and anxiety\n- Releases endorphins that improve mood\n\n5. Visualization techniques\n- Imagine yourself succeeding\n- Picture a calm, positive outcome\n\n6. Gradual exposure\n- Start with small challenges and build up\n- Slowly expose yourself to situations that make you nervous\n\n7. Mindfulness and meditation\n- Learn to stay present and calm\n- Reduce overthinking\n\n8. Get enough sleep\n- Proper rest helps manage stress\n- Improves overall mental resilience\n\n9. Consider professional help\n- Therapists can provide specialized anxiety management techniques\n- Cognitive behavioral therapy can be very effective\n\n10. Learn relaxation techniques\n- Progressive muscle relaxation\n- Meditation\n- Yoga\n\nRemember, managing nervousness is a skill that improves with practice.",
